### Introduction

In this chapter you will learn how to 

* Build your own customized functions 
* Use Loops 
* Apply the bootstrap method 

To meet this chapter's learning objectives, please complete the respective exercise sheet. The instructions below will guide you through the process of solving the exercise sheet.

## Getting ready

### Step 1

Briefly check out the [exercise sheet](C6_exercise.html){target="blank"} for chapter 6 to get an impression of what you need to learn/know to solve it.

### Step 2

Solve task 1-7 of the exercise sheet.

**Comment:** Tasks 4-7 are identical to tasks 4-7 from the Chapter 4 and 5 exercise sheets. To save time, you could copy and paste from the respective solution.

## Functions

### Step 3

Read the following blog post: 

[How to Write Functions in R](https://www.dataquest.io/blog/write-functions-in-r/){target="blank"}

Solve tasks 8-13 of the exercise sheet.

**Comment:** Many of the things you need to solve these tasks were taught in chapter 5 of the SSRC.

## Loops

### Step 4

Watch the following video: [For Loops](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=h987LWDvqlQ&t){target="blank"}

Solve tasks 14-16 of the exercise sheet. 

## Bootstrap

### Step 5

Watch the following video: [Bootstrap Basics](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Xz0x-8-cgaQ&t){target="blank"}

Solve tasks 17-22 of the exercise sheet.

### Step 6

Compare your solutions to the [sample solution](C6_solution.html){target="blank"} for exercise sheet 6.

